jdrasil.algorithms.postprocessing

Class Postprocessor<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • jdrasil.algorithms.postprocessing.Postprocessor<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FlattenTreeDecomposition, ImproveTreeDecomposition, NiceTreeDecomposition

    public abstract class Postprocessor<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    A Postprocessor is a function that maps a given arbitrary tree decomposition to another tree decomposition of the same graph. For instance a Postprocessor may ensure that the decomposition has certain properties (i.\,g., is a \emph{nice} tree decomposition), but a Postprecessor may also \emph{improve} an non-optimal decomposition.

      • processedTreeDecomposition

        protected TreeDecomposition<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>> processedTreeDecomposition
        The processed tree decomposition, i.\,e., the tree decomposition \emph{after} the postprocessing. This may be a pointer to the same object as @see treeDecomposition (if the postprocessing was performed inplace), or may be a new object.

        protected abstract TreeDecomposition<T> postprocessTreeDecomposition()
